summary_text: 1. I was working on the warehouse floor stocking boxes. 2. I felt strange and attributed it to hunger. 3. I felt tightness and pressure in my chest. 4. I leaned against a wall but felt worse. 5. The manager noticed I needed help and approached. 6. I almost fainted but the manager caught me. 7. I learned I had a panic attack and to take better care of myself.

1. I was working on the warehouse floor doing my usual job. 2. I started feeling lightheaded and chalked it up to hunger. 3. I felt chest tightness and pressure getting stronger. 4. I leaned against a wall and felt my heart pounding. 5. I saw spots and sweated as I struggled to breathe. 6. The manager noticed me and rushed to help as I collapsed. 7. I learned it was a panic attack and to take care of myself.
